speare's plays onto the present. Using modernist themes and approaches, he constructs new readings of four Shakespeare plays.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCriticismzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aCriticismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aModernism (Literature)zGreat Britain. 0aModernism (Literature)zUnited States. 4aEngland. 4aLiterary Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172548740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501725487423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501725487/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles